WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.283 --> 00:00:07.217
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

2
00:00:07.350 --> 00:00:10.086
- This is so cool.
Check it out.

3
00:00:10.220 --> 00:00:12.589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

4
00:00:12.722 --> 00:00:15.025
It's a big piece of seal skin.

5
00:00:15.158 --> 00:00:18.662
Seal fat soup. that's
what's for dinner tonight.

6
00:00:18.795 --> 00:00:22.132
- Got a little hare
for a snack today.

7
00:00:22.265 --> 00:00:24.701
Feels right. man.

8
00:00:24.834 --> 00:00:28.271
<i>- I want something where I
can be safe from polar bears.</i>

9
00:00:28.405 --> 00:00:30.540
<i>Being out here this time.
it's a lot different</i>

10
00:00:30.674 --> 00:00:32.142
<i>than being out here
the first time.</i>

11
00:00:32.275 --> 00:00:33.643
I am officially tapping out.

12
00:00:33.777 --> 00:00:40.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13
00:00:41.451 --> 00:00:44.287
<i>narrator: Six of "Alone's"
strongest participants</i>

14
00:00:44.421 --> 00:00:47.090
<i>are about to face
their biggest challenge yet.</i>

15
00:00:47.223 --> 00:00:49.225
<i>- I didn't agree
to do "Alone" again</i>

16
00:00:49.359 --> 00:00:50.794
<i>for a suffering contest.</i>

17
00:00:50.927 --> 00:00:52.395
Oh. my God.

18
00:00:52.529 --> 00:00:54.264
<i>narrator:
With just a few supplies.</i>

19
00:00:54.397 --> 00:00:57.300
<i>they'll push
their skills and bodies</i>

20
00:00:57.434 --> 00:01:00.070
<i>farther than ever before.</i>

21
00:01:00.203 --> 00:01:03.139
<i>Starting later
than any previous season.</i>

22
00:01:03.273 --> 00:01:06.676
<i>and with less time to prepare.
they'll arrive just</i>

23
00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:08.979
<i>as the fierce
North Atlantic winter</i>

24
00:01:09.112 --> 00:01:10.380
<i>is about to begin.</i>

25
00:01:10.513 --> 00:01:11.581
<i>- Winter's my colleague.</i>

26
00:01:11.715 --> 00:01:13.216
Winter's here.

27
00:01:13.350 --> 00:01:16.820
<i>narrator: They'll battle
howling winds. constant rain.</i>

28
00:01:16.953 --> 00:01:20.390
<i>and North America's
most fierce apex predators.</i>

29
00:01:20.523 --> 00:01:22.359
<i>- You're not going
to fight off a polar bear.</i>

30
00:01:22.492 --> 00:01:24.427
<i>It's going to eat you.</i>

31
00:01:24.561 --> 00:01:27.631
<i>narrator: Survive 50 days.
and they'll win their share</i>

32
00:01:27.764 --> 00:01:29.532
<i>of half a million dollars.</i>

33
00:01:29.666 --> 00:01:32.402
- It just doesn't
get any worse.

34
00:01:32.535 --> 00:01:35.572
<i>narrator:
This is "Alone: Frozen."</i>

35
00:01:35.705 --> 00:01:37.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36
00:01:37.807 --> 00:01:40.677
[ice cracking]

37
00:01:40.810 --> 00:01:47.784
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38
00:01:49.319 --> 00:01:50.720
<i>- I don't think anybody
ever sees themselves</i>

39
00:01:50.854 --> 00:01:52.822
<i>not making it to the end.</i>

40
00:01:52.956 --> 00:01:56.059
<i>but I don't look at this
as me quitting.</i>

41
00:01:56.192 --> 00:01:59.396
<i>I look at this as me starting
a new chapter in my life.</i>

42
00:01:59.529 --> 00:02:06.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43
00:02:06.369 --> 00:02:08.638
<i>- This season
we're starting a lot later.</i>

44
00:02:08.772 --> 00:02:09.939
<i>which means we're gonna be</i>

45
00:02:10.073 --> 00:02:13.143
<i>beginning our journey
in winter.</i>

46
00:02:13.276 --> 00:02:14.577
<i>And we're in
one of the most wild</i>

47
00:02:14.711 --> 00:02:16.446
<i>and remote places on Earth.</i>

48
00:02:16.579 --> 00:02:18.481
<i>so it's going to be
real serious</i>

49
00:02:18.615 --> 00:02:20.250
<i>from the moment
we hit the ground.</i>

50
00:02:20.383 --> 00:02:24.521
My last view of people
for a while now.

51
00:02:24.654 --> 00:02:26.022
There it goes!

52
00:02:29.492 --> 00:02:30.560
Oh.

53
00:02:30.693 --> 00:02:31.961
Oh. wow.

54
00:02:33.296 --> 00:02:35.565
<i>- 'Cause the weather is
gonna be harsher here.</i>

55
00:02:35.699 --> 00:02:37.300
<i>Winter is here.</i>

56
00:02:37.434 --> 00:02:39.335
<i>It's only gonna get worse.</i>

57
00:02:39.469 --> 00:02:42.338
<i>That's it for seeing people</i>

58
00:02:42.472 --> 00:02:44.707
for hopefully 50 days.

59
00:02:44.841 --> 00:02:47.143
A pretty remote spot.

60
00:02:47.277 --> 00:02:50.447
And the sun is going down.

61
00:02:50.580 --> 00:02:52.682
I don't have any time
to even get ready

62
00:02:52.816 --> 00:02:54.851
for the night time. really.

63
00:02:54.984 --> 00:02:56.486
<i>- The wetness will be
a real challenge</i>

64
00:02:56.619 --> 00:02:57.854
<i>for us this season.</i>

65
00:02:57.987 --> 00:02:59.222
<i>It just seeps into your bones</i>

66
00:02:59.355 --> 00:03:02.358
<i>and makes it really hard
to stay warm and dry.</i>

67
00:03:02.492 --> 00:03:06.129
<i>Very easy to get hypothermia.
Very easy to get frostbite.</i>

68
00:03:06.262 --> 00:03:09.065
<i>I cannot underestimate
Labrador.</i>

69
00:03:10.600 --> 00:03:12.435
Well. this is it.

70
00:03:23.947 --> 00:03:25.115
[chuckles]

71
00:03:27.183 --> 00:03:28.852
Here I am again.

72
00:03:31.821 --> 00:03:34.524
<i>♪ ♪</i>

73
00:03:34.657 --> 00:03:37.961
God. it's beautiful.

74
00:03:38.094 --> 00:03:40.363
<i>I'm from
the East Coast of Maine.</i>

75
00:03:40.497 --> 00:03:43.800
<i>I feel a real kinship
with being here.</i>

76
00:03:43.933 --> 00:03:45.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

77
00:03:45.702 --> 00:03:48.138
<i>I feel like
I'm walking into a land</i>

78
00:03:48.271 --> 00:03:50.607
<i>that I understand
a little bit better</i>

79
00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:53.777
<i>and I feel connected to.</i>

80
00:03:53.910 --> 00:03:56.379
<i>I was on season eight.</i>

81
00:03:56.513 --> 00:03:58.114
<i>and I lasted for 21 days</i>

82
00:03:58.248 --> 00:04:00.650
<i>before tapping out.</i>

83
00:04:00.783 --> 00:04:03.153
<i>Even though
I was given nothing</i>

84
00:04:03.286 --> 00:04:06.256
<i>but failures
and nothing but starvation.</i>

85
00:04:06.389 --> 00:04:08.291
<i>I felt happy.</i>

86
00:04:08.424 --> 00:04:09.659
Ooh.

87
00:04:09.793 --> 00:04:12.629
<i>What ended my time
during the last season</i>

88
00:04:12.762 --> 00:04:16.699
<i>was my inability
to procure food for myself.</i>

89
00:04:19.302 --> 00:04:22.172
<i>I went in at 120 pounds.</i>

90
00:04:22.305 --> 00:04:23.573
<i>I came out at 98.</i>

91
00:04:23.706 --> 00:04:26.376
Just super weak.

92
00:04:26.509 --> 00:04:29.312
<i>I just couldn't
physically keep up.</i>

93
00:04:29.445 --> 00:04:31.181
I am officially tapping out.

94
00:04:31.314 --> 00:04:32.682
<i>♪ ♪</i>

95
00:04:32.815 --> 00:04:34.851
<i>I really felt like a failure.</i>

96
00:04:34.984 --> 00:04:36.252
[sighs]

97
00:04:39.389 --> 00:04:42.158
<i>Thinking about
all that I gained from it.</i>

98
00:04:42.292 --> 00:04:44.027
<i>all that I learned.</i>

99
00:04:44.160 --> 00:04:45.328
<i>and then to be given</i>

100
00:04:45.461 --> 00:04:50.133
<i>that experience again
is stupefying.</i>

101
00:04:50.266 --> 00:04:52.468
<i>It feels like an honor.</i>

102
00:04:52.602 --> 00:04:53.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

103
00:04:53.903 --> 00:04:57.440
<i>Obviously. I leave
behind my husband again.</i>

104
00:04:57.574 --> 00:05:01.911
<i>But my husband
is 100% supportive</i>

105
00:05:02.045 --> 00:05:03.746
<i>of me in this.</i>

106
00:05:03.880 --> 00:05:06.916
<i>Thinking back to season eight.</i>

107
00:05:07.050 --> 00:05:10.587
<i>I would say I have nothing
but unfinished business.</i>

108
00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:13.823
<i>I felt like
I had barely gotten started.</i>

109
00:05:13.957 --> 00:05:16.092
<i>and my time was over.</i>

110
00:05:16.226 --> 00:05:18.394
<i>For me. this season.</i>

111
00:05:18.528 --> 00:05:21.497
<i>I really want to win the show.</i>

112
00:05:21.631 --> 00:05:24.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

113
00:05:24.667 --> 00:05:27.804
Right now.
there's no time to waste

114
00:05:27.937 --> 00:05:29.606
in not eating

115
00:05:29.739 --> 00:05:32.442
'cause winter is coming.

116
00:05:32.575 --> 00:05:34.877
<i>As soon as we landed.
I could see</i>

117
00:05:35.011 --> 00:05:38.047
<i>all kinds of clamshells
scattering this beach.</i>

118
00:05:38.181 --> 00:05:42.552
<i>and where there's clamshells.
there's clams.</i>

119
00:05:42.685 --> 00:05:45.521
<i>My survival strategy
this time</i>

120
00:05:45.655 --> 00:05:48.424
<i>is to just eat
as much as possible.</i>

121
00:05:48.558 --> 00:05:51.127
<i>to eat like it's my job.</i>

122
00:05:51.261 --> 00:05:54.230
<i>and if I have to eat clams
every single day for 50 days.</i>

123
00:05:54.364 --> 00:05:55.632
<i>so be it.</i>

124
00:05:55.765 --> 00:06:02.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

125
00:06:10.313 --> 00:06:15.551
- Check out
my beautiful little beach.

126
00:06:18.354 --> 00:06:20.390
Wow.

127
00:06:20.523 --> 00:06:24.260
This is really different
from season six.

128
00:06:24.394 --> 00:06:26.195
It is sparse.

129
00:06:26.329 --> 00:06:28.631
It is a whole lot
of bare rock

130
00:06:28.765 --> 00:06:30.400
and teensy little trees.

131
00:06:30.533 --> 00:06:33.436
but this time.
I am on the ocean.

132
00:06:33.569 --> 00:06:36.639
so that already is
a very exciting difference

133
00:06:36.773 --> 00:06:38.541
from season six.

134
00:06:38.675 --> 00:06:40.009
Amazing.

135
00:06:41.177 --> 00:06:43.079
<i>I was the runner-up
on season six of "Alone."</i>

136
00:06:43.212 --> 00:06:46.549
<i>which was the first season
in the Arctic.</i>

137
00:06:46.683 --> 00:06:49.852
<i>I was out there for 73 days.</i>

138
00:06:49.986 --> 00:06:52.889
<i>My time in the Arctic was.
hands-down.</i>

139
00:06:53.022 --> 00:06:55.725
<i>the most powerful experience
of my life.</i>

140
00:06:55.858 --> 00:06:58.961
<i>To have the opportunity
to test my lifetime of skills</i>

141
00:06:59.095 --> 00:07:01.898
<i>and see what it's like
to live 100%</i>

142
00:07:02.031 --> 00:07:04.667
<i>on just what I can make
and do and bring in.</i>

143
00:07:04.801 --> 00:07:08.137
<i>most profound physical.
mental. emotional.</i>

144
00:07:08.271 --> 00:07:10.073
<i>spiritual experience
of my life.</i>

145
00:07:10.206 --> 00:07:11.674
<i>I would wish
an experience like that</i>

146
00:07:11.808 --> 00:07:13.509
<i>for every human alive.</i>

147
00:07:15.244 --> 00:07:17.113
<i>In the last couple of days.</i>

148
00:07:17.246 --> 00:07:19.716
<i>I started to really feel
the effects on my body</i>

149
00:07:19.849 --> 00:07:21.284
<i>and really felt like
I was starting</i>

150
00:07:21.417 --> 00:07:24.053
<i>to approach a cliff edge.</i>

151
00:07:24.187 --> 00:07:27.156
I'm feeling pretty discouraged.

152
00:07:27.290 --> 00:07:29.726
<i>The day I decided to leave.</i>

153
00:07:29.859 --> 00:07:32.295
<i>I knew that it was getting
very. very close</i>

154
00:07:32.428 --> 00:07:34.063
<i>to when I was gonna be
getting pulled.</i>

155
00:07:34.197 --> 00:07:35.898
<i>I knew that there was
a medical check that day.</i>

156
00:07:36.032 --> 00:07:38.401
<i>and I knew that I wasn't
gonna be able to pass it.</i>

157
00:07:38.534 --> 00:07:41.804
I've loved being here
with every fiber of my being.

158
00:07:41.938 --> 00:07:43.506
and I don't really
want to leave.

159
00:07:43.639 --> 00:07:45.808
but my body's done.

160
00:07:45.942 --> 00:07:48.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

161
00:07:48.911 --> 00:07:51.347
<i>I've prepared for
the coming season of "Alone"</i>

162
00:07:51.481 --> 00:07:54.584
<i>by making a bunch of
my own gear to be out there.</i>

163
00:07:54.717 --> 00:07:56.886
Amazing. handmade boots.

164
00:07:57.019 --> 00:07:58.554
<i>When I went last time.</i>

165
00:07:58.688 --> 00:08:01.791
<i>there wasn't anything
really important to me</i>

166
00:08:01.924 --> 00:08:04.027
<i>that I was leaving behind.</i>

167
00:08:04.160 --> 00:08:06.162
A lot of my assets
in being here

168
00:08:06.295 --> 00:08:10.099
are also some of my
greatest sorrows in life.

169
00:08:10.233 --> 00:08:13.236
Not having someone
that I miss so much.

170
00:08:13.369 --> 00:08:16.372
not having
a family depending on me.

171
00:08:16.506 --> 00:08:21.210
<i>And now. I've become
used to a life lived deeply</i>

172
00:08:21.344 --> 00:08:23.513
<i>with another person
who I really love.</i>

173
00:08:23.646 --> 00:08:25.982
<i>My sweetheart Taylor.</i>

174
00:08:26.115 --> 00:08:29.552
<i>whose time and presence
is really valuable to me.</i>

175
00:08:29.685 --> 00:08:32.555
<i>And I am leaving him.
and it's going to be hard</i>

176
00:08:32.688 --> 00:08:34.290
<i>and it's going to
take all of my skill</i>

177
00:08:34.424 --> 00:08:36.526
<i>to make this come together.</i>

178
00:08:36.659 --> 00:08:38.528
But if I can pull it off.

179
00:08:38.661 --> 00:08:41.764
<i>then this is gonna be
very well worth</i>

180
00:08:41.898 --> 00:08:45.134
<i>the extra effort
it's gonna take me.</i>

181
00:08:45.268 --> 00:08:46.969
Holy crap.

182
00:08:47.103 --> 00:08:48.805
There's a water bottle.

183
00:08:48.938 --> 00:08:50.373
Hell. yes.

184
00:08:50.506 --> 00:08:53.876
One of the first things to
greet me being a water bottle.

185
00:08:54.010 --> 00:08:56.012
pretty dang exciting.

186
00:08:56.145 --> 00:08:58.014
Like. really exciting.

187
00:08:58.147 --> 00:09:01.417
Portable water is huge
in a survival situation.

188
00:09:01.551 --> 00:09:02.418
Huge.

189
00:09:02.552 --> 00:09:07.523
<i>♪ ♪</i>

190
00:09:07.657 --> 00:09:09.425
I would love
to harvest some food.

191
00:09:09.559 --> 00:09:12.562
but my priority right now
is not in fact dinner.

192
00:09:12.695 --> 00:09:15.465
It is finding shelter location
for tonight

193
00:09:15.598 --> 00:09:18.534
because the sun is almost down.

194
00:09:18.668 --> 00:09:20.203
It is late in the day.

195
00:09:20.336 --> 00:09:22.271
and I don't know anything

196
00:09:22.405 --> 00:09:23.840
about this area
besides this beach

197
00:09:23.973 --> 00:09:24.974
right in front of me.

198
00:09:25.107 --> 00:09:26.676
so it's time to do
a little exploring

199
00:09:26.809 --> 00:09:29.412
and then work on getting
my temporary shelter up.

200
00:09:29.545 --> 00:09:36.552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

201
00:09:45.895 --> 00:09:48.331
- It's kind of
a unique area.

202
00:09:48.464 --> 00:09:50.433
I don't even have time

203
00:09:50.566 --> 00:09:53.069
to see what the resources are.

204
00:09:53.202 --> 00:09:55.204
I'm just going to find
a spot

205
00:09:55.338 --> 00:09:58.241
<i>between a few trees</i>

206
00:09:58.374 --> 00:10:00.743
<i>and set up. temporarily.
my tarp.</i>

207
00:10:00.877 --> 00:10:03.513
Throw my sleeping bag down
and hope for the best.

208
00:10:03.646 --> 00:10:05.548
I don't want to see
any polar bears tonight.

209
00:10:05.681 --> 00:10:07.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

210
00:10:07.283 --> 00:10:09.285
<i>The motivating factor for me</i>

211
00:10:09.418 --> 00:10:11.087
<i>was to have a second chance.</i>

212
00:10:11.220 --> 00:10:13.723
<i>I want to see
if experiences I've had</i>

213
00:10:13.856 --> 00:10:15.157
<i>in the last few years.</i>

214
00:10:15.291 --> 00:10:18.461
<i>if I can make it a lot easier
this round</i>

215
00:10:18.594 --> 00:10:20.329
<i>and not struggle as much.</i>

216
00:10:22.465 --> 00:10:24.400
Well. we're sailing.

217
00:10:24.534 --> 00:10:26.169
Yee-haw.

218
00:10:26.302 --> 00:10:29.839
<i>I was on season three
in Patagonia.</i>

219
00:10:29.972 --> 00:10:32.241
<i>and I went 51 days.</i>

220
00:10:32.375 --> 00:10:33.676
Got my homemade comb.

221
00:10:33.809 --> 00:10:35.244
<i>♪ ♪</i>

222
00:10:35.378 --> 00:10:37.580
I'll try to get the knots out.

223
00:10:37.713 --> 00:10:39.615
<i>It was very difficult
at the end</i>

224
00:10:39.749 --> 00:10:42.385
<i>because I hadn't eaten
for quite a long time.</i>

225
00:10:42.518 --> 00:10:45.421
<i>I fell in the lake.</i>

226
00:10:45.555 --> 00:10:49.058
Oh. no. no. no. that's cold.

227
00:10:49.191 --> 00:10:50.593
Oh!

228
00:10:50.760 --> 00:10:52.328
I got to get to the fire.

229
00:10:52.461 --> 00:10:54.063
Ow. my feet.

230
00:10:54.197 --> 00:10:55.831
<i>After that day.</i>

231
00:10:55.965 --> 00:10:57.600
<i>I just went downhill</i>

232
00:10:57.733 --> 00:10:59.702
<i>and realized
that I had to tap</i>

233
00:10:59.835 --> 00:11:01.704
<i>because I wasn't
thinking straight anymore.</i>

234
00:11:01.837 --> 00:11:03.873
<i>and I just couldn't warm up
after that.</i>

235
00:11:04.006 --> 00:11:07.910
Hypothermia set in.
No fish for a week.

236
00:11:08.010 --> 00:11:09.645
Just every time I get up.

237
00:11:09.779 --> 00:11:10.713
it's like I'm going to faint.

238
00:11:10.846 --> 00:11:12.949
I just got no energy.
just done.

239
00:11:14.250 --> 00:11:18.421
<i>Well. I can't say that
it changed my life completely</i>

240
00:11:18.554 --> 00:11:21.123
<i>because I've spent
most my life in the bush.</i>

241
00:11:21.257 --> 00:11:22.725
I drink right out
of these creeks.

242
00:11:22.858 --> 00:11:24.527
They come right out
of the Rockies.

243
00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:28.431
<i>So now at almost 59.
I'm twice as old</i>

244
00:11:28.564 --> 00:11:30.566
<i>as almost the rest
of the competitors.</i>

245
00:11:30.700 --> 00:11:33.736
<i>but with age comes wisdom.</i>

246
00:11:33.869 --> 00:11:35.905
<i>I won't be as anxious
this time</i>

247
00:11:36.038 --> 00:11:38.007
<i>because I've been through it
once already.</i>

248
00:11:38.140 --> 00:11:39.375
<i>Still be a challenge.</i>

249
00:11:39.508 --> 00:11:42.311
<i>but now. I think
I'll be more prepared to deal</i>

250
00:11:42.445 --> 00:11:45.247
<i>with the challenges a little
differently this time.</i>

251
00:11:45.381 --> 00:11:48.718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

252
00:11:48.851 --> 00:11:51.287
I will feel safer
in the trees here.

253
00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:53.155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

254
00:11:53.289 --> 00:11:55.091
<i>The only concern that I had</i>

255
00:11:55.224 --> 00:11:57.126
<i>when I found out
where the location was</i>

256
00:11:57.259 --> 00:11:59.295
<i>was the polar bears.</i>

257
00:11:59.428 --> 00:12:02.131
When they grab a hold
of you at night by the leg.

258
00:12:02.265 --> 00:12:03.733
<i>it's not going to be pretty.</i>

259
00:12:05.635 --> 00:12:09.472
That is a very primitive

260
00:12:09.605 --> 00:12:12.308
setup of a tarp
if I can say so myself.

261
00:12:12.441 --> 00:12:15.177
I mean.
I just slapped it together.

262
00:12:15.311 --> 00:12:17.747
but it'll do for tonight.

263
00:12:17.880 --> 00:12:19.248
Tomorrow is a different day.

264
00:12:19.382 --> 00:12:21.751
<i>♪ ♪</i>

265
00:12:21.884 --> 00:12:22.752
<i>Got to get firewood.</i>

266
00:12:22.885 --> 00:12:25.454
<i>Sun's going to go down soon.</i>

267
00:12:25.588 --> 00:12:27.423
<i>This year.
even though we know</i>

268
00:12:27.556 --> 00:12:30.259
<i>we're only supposed
to go 50 days.</i>

269
00:12:30.393 --> 00:12:32.595
<i>conditions are gonna be
wintertime.</i>

270
00:12:32.728 --> 00:12:35.097
<i>So we know
it's gonna get cold</i>

271
00:12:35.231 --> 00:12:37.199
<i>and the plants
are gonna die out.</i>

272
00:12:37.333 --> 00:12:41.337
<i>and it's just not gonna be
an easy goal no matter what.</i>

273
00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:42.872
<i>Can't even predict
the weather here.</i>

274
00:12:43.005 --> 00:12:44.507
<i>♪ ♪</i>

275
00:12:44.640 --> 00:12:46.242
Oh. boy.

276
00:12:46.375 --> 00:12:48.878
So there is bears around.
I guess.

277
00:12:49.011 --> 00:12:50.313
<i>♪ ♪</i>

278
00:12:50.446 --> 00:12:53.215
So the bear. I can see.
came through here.

279
00:12:53.349 --> 00:12:56.319
like. just recently.

280
00:12:56.452 --> 00:13:00.122
Sure be something
if a 1.500 pound polar bear

281
00:13:00.256 --> 00:13:03.125
came walking up the beach.

282
00:13:03.259 --> 00:13:05.828
I do not want
to see a polar bear.

283
00:13:05.961 --> 00:13:07.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

284
00:13:11.367 --> 00:13:14.070
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

285
00:13:14.203 --> 00:13:21.177
<i>♪ ♪</i>

286
00:13:36.659 --> 00:13:39.161
- All right.
I have my ridge pole

287
00:13:39.295 --> 00:13:40.629
and my tripod up.

288
00:13:40.763 --> 00:13:44.166
and they are not
the most beautiful.

289
00:13:44.300 --> 00:13:46.335
but they will serve
for the first night.

290
00:13:46.469 --> 00:13:48.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

291
00:13:48.304 --> 00:13:49.805
It is so dang damp

292
00:13:49.939 --> 00:13:53.175
that I want to get everything
under cover.

293
00:13:53.309 --> 00:13:55.711
<i>This environment is one
where we're gonna be exposed</i>

294
00:13:55.845 --> 00:13:59.281
<i>to gale-force winds.
horizontal rain and snow.</i>

295
00:13:59.415 --> 00:14:01.550
<i>It's an area
with really intense weather.</i>

296
00:14:01.684 --> 00:14:03.352
<i>really unpredictable weather.</i>

297
00:14:03.486 --> 00:14:04.954
<i>The challenges of this place</i>

298
00:14:05.087 --> 00:14:07.923
<i>are going to be firewood
and tinder</i>

299
00:14:08.057 --> 00:14:09.792
<i>because it is wet. wet. wet.</i>

300
00:14:09.925 --> 00:14:11.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

301
00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:14.430
<i>A wet. cold climate is way
more intimidating to me</i>

302
00:14:14.563 --> 00:14:16.098
<i>than a dry cold.</i>

303
00:14:16.232 --> 00:14:19.535
<i>Wet cold is a really different
kind of cold than dry cold.</i>

304
00:14:19.668 --> 00:14:21.504
<i>It's way more penetrating.</i>

305
00:14:21.637 --> 00:14:25.274
<i>and it can just really
sap you a lot more.</i>

306
00:14:25.407 --> 00:14:27.543
It's good for tonight.
maybe tomorrow night.

307
00:14:27.676 --> 00:14:29.245
but I do not want to be
in this thing

308
00:14:29.378 --> 00:14:30.913
when it starts raining.

309
00:14:32.415 --> 00:14:34.417
I am planning on
hanging the tarp

310
00:14:34.550 --> 00:14:37.019
so that some of it comes
underneath the shelter

311
00:14:37.153 --> 00:14:39.755
and I can be putting
my sleeping bag on the tarp

312
00:14:39.889 --> 00:14:41.690
rather than
on the moist ground.

313
00:14:42.892 --> 00:14:45.327
I am ready to bed
down for the night.

314
00:14:49.431 --> 00:14:51.066
You are not going
to believe this.

315
00:14:53.369 --> 00:14:55.371
The aurora borealis
is happening.

316
00:14:55.504 --> 00:14:57.039
<i>♪ ♪</i>

317
00:14:57.173 --> 00:15:00.443
<i>They are what greet me when
I step out of the shelter.</i>

318
00:15:00.576 --> 00:15:01.977
This is a very good sign.

319
00:15:02.111 --> 00:15:05.080
I feel so blessed
and so welcome here.

320
00:15:05.214 --> 00:15:12.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

321
00:15:20.062 --> 00:15:21.130
<i>- So last night.</i>

322
00:15:21.263 --> 00:15:24.133
I just camped here
on the beach.

323
00:15:26.168 --> 00:15:29.138
Here's my little setup
over there.

324
00:15:30.206 --> 00:15:34.243
I woke up
in the middle of the night.

325
00:15:34.376 --> 00:15:38.047
and I looked out.
and the aurora was out.

326
00:15:38.180 --> 00:15:39.782
and it was so cool.

327
00:15:39.915 --> 00:15:41.050
That was really neat.

328
00:15:41.183 --> 00:15:43.352
I haven't seen that
since I lived in Alaska.

329
00:15:44.653 --> 00:15:47.623
<i>It's a gorgeous day today.</i>

330
00:15:47.756 --> 00:15:50.059
<i>but with weather coming in.</i>

331
00:15:50.192 --> 00:15:52.394
<i>I really need to make sure</i>

332
00:15:52.528 --> 00:15:55.331
<i>I've got a weatherproof place
to sleep.</i>

333
00:15:55.464 --> 00:15:58.701
So I need to get
my shelter sorted out.

334
00:15:58.834 --> 00:16:00.836
<i>♪ ♪</i>

335
00:16:00.970 --> 00:16:03.772
<i>One of our big challenges
will be</i>

336
00:16:03.906 --> 00:16:05.641
<i>not just the cold weather</i>

337
00:16:05.774 --> 00:16:09.078
<i>but the very high humidity
with high winds.</i>

338
00:16:10.446 --> 00:16:13.349
<i>When you're
in very wet conditions</i>

339
00:16:13.482 --> 00:16:16.452
<i>coupled with cold
and high humidity.</i>

340
00:16:16.585 --> 00:16:20.055
<i>you can get frostbite
quite easily.</i>

341
00:16:20.189 --> 00:16:25.094
<i>so you're going
to be constantly tasked</i>

342
00:16:25.227 --> 00:16:27.796
<i>with keeping dry.</i>

343
00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:30.199
<i>Finding a camp
that has all the things</i>

344
00:16:30.332 --> 00:16:33.202
<i>that you need
but it still has good access</i>

345
00:16:33.335 --> 00:16:36.105
<i>is such an important priority.</i>

346
00:16:36.238 --> 00:16:38.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

347
00:16:40.676 --> 00:16:43.812
<i>In Labrador. there are lots
of black bear</i>

348
00:16:43.946 --> 00:16:45.547
<i>and polar bear.</i>

349
00:16:45.681 --> 00:16:48.584
<i>which is very alarming.</i>

350
00:16:48.717 --> 00:16:49.785
<i>What do they say?</i>

351
00:16:49.919 --> 00:16:51.587
<i>Black. fight back.</i>

352
00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:53.389
<i>Brown. lie down.</i>

353
00:16:53.522 --> 00:16:55.791
<i>White. good night.</i>

354
00:16:55.925 --> 00:16:57.426
<i>The last thing
in the world you want</i>

355
00:16:57.559 --> 00:16:59.628
<i>is a polar bear
knowing you're there.</i>

356
00:16:59.762 --> 00:17:03.699
<i>So I need to build my shelter
fairly quickly</i>

357
00:17:03.832 --> 00:17:07.670
<i>for protection
against the weather and bears.</i>

358
00:17:07.803 --> 00:17:08.804
Okay.

359
00:17:08.938 --> 00:17:11.473
Well. I found a spot...

360
00:17:13.275 --> 00:17:16.278
That I think would be suitable
for a shelter.

361
00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:20.249
[saw scraping]

362
00:17:20.382 --> 00:17:22.084
Missing my chainsaw right now.

363
00:17:22.217 --> 00:17:23.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

364
00:17:23.886 --> 00:17:27.056
<i>Last season. I was so fixated
on shelter. shelter. shelter</i>

365
00:17:27.189 --> 00:17:29.224
<i>that I was burning through
so many calories.</i>

366
00:17:29.358 --> 00:17:32.361
<i>so I just have
a different mentality now.</i>

367
00:17:32.494 --> 00:17:37.533
<i>My strategy is to keep it
simple and small.</i>

368
00:17:37.666 --> 00:17:40.903
<i>The smaller I can make it.
the warmer it will be.</i>

369
00:17:41.036 --> 00:17:45.808
<i>♪ ♪</i>

370
00:17:45.941 --> 00:17:47.509
That should do it.

371
00:17:50.245 --> 00:17:52.615
Yeah. nice.

372
00:17:52.748 --> 00:17:54.249
<i>The shelter design
is very simple.</i>

373
00:17:54.383 --> 00:17:59.321
<i>So it's basically a center
ridge line support beam</i>

374
00:17:59.455 --> 00:18:01.623
<i>that falls to an A-frame.</i>

375
00:18:01.757 --> 00:18:07.062
<i>♪ ♪</i>

376
00:18:07.196 --> 00:18:10.599
<i>It's completely covered
to the ground</i>

377
00:18:10.733 --> 00:18:13.569
<i>by the tarp on either side.</i>

378
00:18:13.702 --> 00:18:16.105
That's the right height for me.

379
00:18:16.238 --> 00:18:17.539
Yeah.

380
00:18:17.673 --> 00:18:21.510
<i>And there are ribs
that are internally attached</i>

381
00:18:21.643 --> 00:18:25.114
<i>to the support beam
across the center.</i>

382
00:18:25.247 --> 00:18:27.449
[exhales]
Two down. a million to go.

383
00:18:28.651 --> 00:18:31.086
All right. let me go check
on the fire real quick.

384
00:18:41.830 --> 00:18:43.632
I'm hearing
something over there.

385
00:18:43.766 --> 00:18:46.035
<i>[ominous music]</i>

386
00:18:46.168 --> 00:18:48.003
<i>♪ ♪</i>

387
00:18:48.137 --> 00:18:49.338
It sounds big.

388
00:18:49.471 --> 00:18:52.508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

389
00:18:52.641 --> 00:18:53.976
I'm gonna go just take a peek.

390
00:18:54.109 --> 00:19:01.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

391
00:19:07.322 --> 00:19:08.524
Oh. my God.

392
00:19:15.230 --> 00:19:18.100
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

393
00:19:18.233 --> 00:19:25.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

394
00:19:32.014 --> 00:19:33.816
<i>- I'm hearing
something over there.</i>

395
00:19:33.949 --> 00:19:34.817
<i>♪ ♪</i>

396
00:19:34.950 --> 00:19:35.918
Sounds big.

397
00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:39.121
<i>♪ ♪</i>

398
00:19:39.254 --> 00:19:40.756
I'm gonna go just take a peek.

399
00:19:40.889 --> 00:19:43.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

400
00:19:44.026 --> 00:19:45.494
Oh. my God.

401
00:19:45.627 --> 00:19:47.429
Please don't be a bear.

402
00:19:47.563 --> 00:19:51.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

403
00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:52.801
[bleep]

404
00:19:52.935 --> 00:19:54.436
Just the water.

405
00:19:54.570 --> 00:19:56.772
It's really up.

406
00:19:56.905 --> 00:19:57.940
Dang.

407
00:20:01.176 --> 00:20:02.478
Holy mackerel.

408
00:20:05.681 --> 00:20:08.050
That was kind of scary.

409
00:20:08.183 --> 00:20:10.185
I don't know.
I'm nervous about...

410
00:20:10.319 --> 00:20:13.422
my shelter situation.

411
00:20:13.555 --> 00:20:14.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

412
00:20:15.023 --> 00:20:18.093
<i>I'm hoping that this weather
continues right now.</i>

413
00:20:18.227 --> 00:20:21.730
<i>but I don't know.
those clouds.</i>

414
00:20:21.864 --> 00:20:24.533
<i>I need to make
my shelter pretty strong.</i>

415
00:20:24.666 --> 00:20:26.201
<i>I want it sturdy enough</i>

416
00:20:26.335 --> 00:20:28.036
<i>that it can withstand wind</i>

417
00:20:28.170 --> 00:20:30.539
<i>and take on some snow</i>

418
00:20:30.672 --> 00:20:32.574
<i>because Labrador
has some big storms</i>

419
00:20:32.708 --> 00:20:34.743
<i>and can get
a dumping of snow.</i>

420
00:20:36.245 --> 00:20:39.648
<i>The weather can change
in a moment.</i>

421
00:20:39.781 --> 00:20:42.785
<i>so you just have
to be prepared.</i>

422
00:20:42.918 --> 00:20:49.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

423
00:20:59.935 --> 00:21:01.336
<i>- Now the weather got
a little nasty.</i>

424
00:21:01.470 --> 00:21:03.472
It's kind of windy out.

425
00:21:03.605 --> 00:21:06.708
I've been sleeping
just on the ground.

426
00:21:06.842 --> 00:21:09.811
not feeling great
about it either.

427
00:21:09.945 --> 00:21:12.281
but the lean-to.
even though it's--

428
00:21:12.414 --> 00:21:14.616
it's not really security
in a sense.

429
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:17.352
but it does make
you kind of feel better.

430
00:21:17.486 --> 00:21:21.156
And hope for the best
as far as the bears go.

431
00:21:21.290 --> 00:21:23.425
[laughs]

432
00:21:23.559 --> 00:21:25.294
That's for sure.

433
00:21:25.427 --> 00:21:28.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

434
00:21:28.397 --> 00:21:31.867
<i>We're not very far
into my stay here.</i>

435
00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:35.337
<i>and I'm already going hungry.</i>

436
00:21:35.470 --> 00:21:38.140
<i>I haven't eaten
anything today.</i>

437
00:21:38.273 --> 00:21:40.576
<i>so I should get out
and get some mussels.</i>

438
00:21:40.709 --> 00:21:44.379
About halfway
between this rock escarpment

439
00:21:44.513 --> 00:21:47.249
and the shore
is the best mussels. I find.

440
00:21:47.382 --> 00:21:49.251
<i>♪ ♪</i>

441
00:21:49.384 --> 00:21:51.787
<i>My family.
they were outdoors people.</i>

442
00:21:51.920 --> 00:21:53.889
<i>but the survival
and the things.</i>

443
00:21:54.022 --> 00:21:56.959
<i>I developed on my own
through reading.</i>

444
00:21:57.092 --> 00:21:59.661
<i>At about 12.
I bought a book.</i>

445
00:21:59.795 --> 00:22:02.364
<i>Bradford Angier. "How to
Stay Alive in the Woods."</i>

446
00:22:02.497 --> 00:22:04.333
<i>and I started reading
that book</i>

447
00:22:04.466 --> 00:22:06.368
<i>and became fascinated.</i>

448
00:22:06.501 --> 00:22:09.104
<i>so I practiced
all those skills</i>

449
00:22:09.238 --> 00:22:11.240
<i>on the acreage where we lived.</i>

450
00:22:11.373 --> 00:22:13.575
<i>And after that.
it just became</i>

451
00:22:13.709 --> 00:22:16.345
<i>almost an obsession.
I would say.</i>

452
00:22:16.478 --> 00:22:17.679
<i>Even to this day.</i>

453
00:22:17.813 --> 00:22:20.849
<i>I'm always trying to come up
with a new idea.</i>

454
00:22:20.983 --> 00:22:22.651
<i>You know.
you can never learn too much.</i>

455
00:22:22.784 --> 00:22:24.353
<i>and you're always learning.</i>

456
00:22:24.486 --> 00:22:27.556
<i>So here I am. going to be 59
in a couple of months.</i>

457
00:22:27.689 --> 00:22:29.124
<i>and I'm still trying
to come up</i>

458
00:22:29.258 --> 00:22:31.893
<i>with fishing ideas. traps.</i>

459
00:22:32.027 --> 00:22:34.563
<i>It just never ends.</i>

460
00:22:34.696 --> 00:22:35.831
That's all good.

461
00:22:35.964 --> 00:22:38.700
but I got to get something
more substantial

462
00:22:38.834 --> 00:22:40.769
than just mussels.

463
00:22:40.903 --> 00:22:43.138
So I got to try fishing.

464
00:22:43.272 --> 00:22:45.907
try mussels for bait.

465
00:22:46.041 --> 00:22:47.476
<i>♪ ♪</i>

466
00:22:47.609 --> 00:22:52.080
<i>I'm the kind of guy
that I rely heavily on fish</i>

467
00:22:52.214 --> 00:22:54.883
<i>when I venture on my own.</i>

468
00:22:55.017 --> 00:22:57.452
<i>If I'm not catching fish.</i>

469
00:22:57.586 --> 00:22:59.721
<i>then I really struggle.</i>

470
00:22:59.855 --> 00:23:02.457
<i>but I think there's gonna be
a lot of fish in the ocean.</i>

471
00:23:02.591 --> 00:23:08.096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

472
00:23:09.831 --> 00:23:11.033
<i>♪ ♪</i>

473
00:23:11.166 --> 00:23:12.668
Now I'm snagged.

474
00:23:12.801 --> 00:23:15.470
<i>♪ ♪</i>

475
00:23:15.604 --> 00:23:18.407
Or it's kelp again or seaweed.

476
00:23:18.540 --> 00:23:20.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

477
00:23:21.109 --> 00:23:22.377
<i>The kelp grows out</i>

478
00:23:22.511 --> 00:23:26.315
<i>just about as far as I can
throw my hand line out.</i>

479
00:23:26.448 --> 00:23:28.016
<i>♪ ♪</i>

480
00:23:28.150 --> 00:23:30.319
<i>This is about
the worst fishing spot</i>

481
00:23:30.452 --> 00:23:33.789
<i>I've seen in my lifetime.</i>

482
00:23:33.922 --> 00:23:35.824
<i>The tide is
starting to come in.</i>

483
00:23:35.957 --> 00:23:39.928
<i>but fortunately. I got
those nice big mussels here.</i>

484
00:23:40.062 --> 00:23:43.365
Time to boil up my mussels

485
00:23:43.498 --> 00:23:45.967
and keep these muscles up
with those mussels.

486
00:23:46.101 --> 00:23:49.838
<i>♪ ♪</i>

487
00:23:49.971 --> 00:23:52.040
And where's the pot?

488
00:23:52.174 --> 00:23:54.876
And this is going to be
over my boots soon now too.

489
00:23:55.010 --> 00:23:57.846
Look it.
the tide's coming in now.

490
00:23:57.979 --> 00:23:59.314
I seem to have put it down.

491
00:23:59.448 --> 00:24:02.217
Remember when I was
trying to find the bait?

492
00:24:02.351 --> 00:24:03.385
[sighs]

493
00:24:03.518 --> 00:24:04.786
Man. I tell you.

494
00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:08.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

495
00:24:08.223 --> 00:24:09.991
If I lose that pot.

496
00:24:10.125 --> 00:24:13.362
I won't even be able to have
my mussel soup

497
00:24:13.495 --> 00:24:15.497
in the morning.

498
00:24:15.630 --> 00:24:19.001
<i>I can't make my teas.
Can't boil water.</i>

499
00:24:19.134 --> 00:24:21.303
<i>There's just a lot
of things I can't do now</i>

500
00:24:21.436 --> 00:24:24.306
<i>if I don't have that pot.</i>

501
00:24:24.439 --> 00:24:26.675
These are the kind of things
I always end up doing.

502
00:24:26.808 --> 00:24:28.076
I'm telling you.

503
00:24:28.210 --> 00:24:29.945
<i>♪ ♪</i>

504
00:24:30.078 --> 00:24:33.148
I don't see why I would
do something so stupid.

505
00:24:39.254 --> 00:24:42.157
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

506
00:24:42.290 --> 00:24:49.331
<i>♪ ♪</i>

507
00:24:58.607 --> 00:25:00.275
<i>- I put my pot down.</i>

508
00:25:00.409 --> 00:25:02.644
<i>I went and did
a bit of fishing.</i>

509
00:25:02.778 --> 00:25:05.514
<i>and now I can't remember
where I put the pot.</i>

510
00:25:06.548 --> 00:25:09.484
So I've been going through
the scenes on the camera.

511
00:25:09.618 --> 00:25:12.254
trying to identify the rocks.

512
00:25:12.387 --> 00:25:14.556
and I think this is the rock.

513
00:25:14.689 --> 00:25:16.825
but I don't see
the pot anywhere.

514
00:25:19.027 --> 00:25:20.328
I might have left it.

515
00:25:20.462 --> 00:25:23.031
Then the tide come in
and swept it away.

516
00:25:23.165 --> 00:25:29.071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

517
00:25:29.204 --> 00:25:31.706
This is about as bad of--

518
00:25:31.840 --> 00:25:33.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

519
00:25:33.341 --> 00:25:36.645
It just doesn't get
any worse than this.

520
00:25:36.778 --> 00:25:38.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

521
00:25:38.680 --> 00:25:40.282
<i>Can't catch fish.</i>

522
00:25:40.415 --> 00:25:43.385
<i>I'm getting anxious
about what's gonna happen</i>

523
00:25:43.518 --> 00:25:45.353
<i>in the future here</i>

524
00:25:45.487 --> 00:25:47.656
<i>because it keeps putting me
back into Patagonia</i>

525
00:25:47.789 --> 00:25:49.424
<i>where I suffered so bad.</i>

526
00:25:49.558 --> 00:25:50.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

527
00:25:50.992 --> 00:25:52.861
<i>It's just an overwhelming
kind of a feeling</i>

528
00:25:52.994 --> 00:25:55.697
<i>that you're not in control
of your own situation.</i>

529
00:25:55.831 --> 00:25:57.666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

530
00:25:57.799 --> 00:26:01.403
Okay.
I think I see it over here.

531
00:26:01.536 --> 00:26:03.338
Thank goodness. here it is.

532
00:26:10.178 --> 00:26:13.248
Hang on to that pot. Greg.

533
00:26:13.381 --> 00:26:20.055
<i>♪ ♪</i>

534
00:26:29.431 --> 00:26:32.400
<i>- It is a chilly.
overcast morning.</i>

535
00:26:32.534 --> 00:26:34.870
So today is the day
I'm going to start working

536
00:26:35.003 --> 00:26:36.271
on my permanent shelter.

537
00:26:36.404 --> 00:26:37.706
It's going to be
a serious push.

538
00:26:37.839 --> 00:26:39.107
It's going to be
a lot of work.

539
00:26:39.241 --> 00:26:40.475
and I know
that weather is coming.

540
00:26:40.609 --> 00:26:43.245
so definitely have
a fire lit under me

541
00:26:43.378 --> 00:26:45.046
to get that shelter done

542
00:26:45.180 --> 00:26:46.181
<i>before that weather comes.</i>

543
00:26:46.314 --> 00:26:48.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

544
00:26:48.250 --> 00:26:49.885
<i>I have been racking
my brain</i>

545
00:26:50.018 --> 00:26:51.520
<i>thinking about
how in the world</i>

546
00:26:51.653 --> 00:26:53.688
<i>I am going to build a shelter</i>

547
00:26:53.822 --> 00:26:55.957
<i>that is secure against
the intense weather</i>

548
00:26:56.091 --> 00:26:57.292
<i>we're getting here.</i>

549
00:26:57.425 --> 00:27:00.428
<i>There's not
a lot of building materials.</i>

550
00:27:00.562 --> 00:27:02.063
<i>So walking around.</i>

551
00:27:02.197 --> 00:27:05.000
<i>I came upon a spot
with a rock edge</i>

552
00:27:05.133 --> 00:27:06.935
<i>to one side.
and a little hollow</i>

553
00:27:07.068 --> 00:27:09.237
<i>just on the down slope side
of it.</i>

554
00:27:09.371 --> 00:27:11.072
<i>I think I'm going
to use this spot</i>

555
00:27:11.206 --> 00:27:14.042
<i>and actually build
against the rock cliff.</i>

556
00:27:14.175 --> 00:27:15.544
If you haven't noticed.

557
00:27:15.677 --> 00:27:17.779
it's gotten
a little wet and windy.

558
00:27:17.913 --> 00:27:21.283
but you gotta work

559
00:27:21.416 --> 00:27:23.919
with the conditions you got.

560
00:27:24.052 --> 00:27:26.321
<i>Using this rock
is going to give me</i>

561
00:27:26.454 --> 00:27:28.890
<i>two walls of a shelter.</i>

562
00:27:29.024 --> 00:27:30.992
<i>which is going to cut in half</i>

563
00:27:31.126 --> 00:27:33.628
<i>the other material
that I need.</i>

564
00:27:33.762 --> 00:27:36.965
My hands are really taking
a beating right now.

565
00:27:37.098 --> 00:27:39.234
<i>I'm nervous
about this environment.</i>

566
00:27:39.367 --> 00:27:42.704
<i>I feel less connected
to this place than I did</i>

567
00:27:42.837 --> 00:27:45.040
<i>to the Northwest Territories.</i>

568
00:27:45.173 --> 00:27:48.577
<i>It's feeling harder
than the place I was before.</i>

569
00:27:48.710 --> 00:27:50.679
<i>and that place
felt freaking hard.</i>

570
00:27:50.812 --> 00:27:57.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

571
00:27:57.152 --> 00:27:59.054
I only have
two and a half sides.

572
00:27:59.187 --> 00:28:00.956
basically.
of my shelter completed.

573
00:28:01.089 --> 00:28:03.692
I managed to get
the tarp over it.

574
00:28:03.825 --> 00:28:05.260
and eventually I'm going to do

575
00:28:05.393 --> 00:28:07.862
a combination of logs and sod.

576
00:28:07.996 --> 00:28:11.600
<i>My hand is really
bothering me with tendonitis</i>

577
00:28:11.733 --> 00:28:13.602
<i>from all of that digging
by hand</i>

578
00:28:13.735 --> 00:28:15.804
<i>and chopping
and all of the things</i>

579
00:28:15.937 --> 00:28:18.039
<i>that are required
for daily life here.</i>

580
00:28:18.173 --> 00:28:19.608
<i>♪ ♪</i>

581
00:28:19.741 --> 00:28:23.979
<i>I am ready to get
under shelter and protected.</i>

582
00:28:24.112 --> 00:28:31.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

583
00:28:40.195 --> 00:28:42.197
- I thought this canvas
tarp was going to be good.

584
00:28:42.330 --> 00:28:46.067
but now my down-filled
sleeping bag is wet.

585
00:28:46.201 --> 00:28:48.136
<i>Oh. that just irritates me.</i>

586
00:28:48.269 --> 00:28:50.972
<i>You buy an expensive tarp.
and it leaks.</i>

587
00:28:51.106 --> 00:28:53.275
<i>I got to try
to dry things out.</i>

588
00:28:53.408 --> 00:28:55.510
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

589
00:28:55.644 --> 00:28:57.646
I'm going to have to use
the black tarp

590
00:28:57.779 --> 00:28:59.881
that's for the camera gear.

591
00:29:00.015 --> 00:29:02.317
and then bring the camera gear
into my shelter.

592
00:29:02.450 --> 00:29:04.919
get a fire going inside

593
00:29:05.053 --> 00:29:07.289
so I can try to dry
some stuff out

594
00:29:07.422 --> 00:29:10.392
because I don't think that this
weather is going to let up.

595
00:29:10.525 --> 00:29:12.961
I think it's going to
just keep raining all day.

596
00:29:13.094 --> 00:29:14.062
That's what it looks like.

597
00:29:14.195 --> 00:29:17.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

598
00:29:17.365 --> 00:29:19.434
Look at how wet
my sleeping bag is.

599
00:29:19.567 --> 00:29:21.436
It's just weighs a ton.

600
00:29:21.569 --> 00:29:24.005
Of course. it's down-filled.

601
00:29:24.139 --> 00:29:26.875
So now. I'm going to have to--

602
00:29:27.008 --> 00:29:28.710
I hope I can dry it out.

603
00:29:28.843 --> 00:29:30.445
<i>♪ ♪</i>

604
00:29:30.578 --> 00:29:34.249
<i>This is much harder
than I thought it would be.</i>

605
00:29:34.382 --> 00:29:36.985
<i>The mental struggle
is extreme.</i>

606
00:29:37.118 --> 00:29:39.154
<i>That's what I'm finding
the hardest</i>

607
00:29:39.287 --> 00:29:42.824
<i>is just mentally dealing
with the failures.</i>

608
00:29:42.957 --> 00:29:44.325
<i>And I do have to be careful.</i>

609
00:29:44.459 --> 00:29:45.960
<i>I'm not 30.</i>

610
00:29:46.094 --> 00:29:47.729
<i>A lot of my friends.</i>

611
00:29:47.862 --> 00:29:49.297
<i>they've been telling me
for years.</i>

612
00:29:49.431 --> 00:29:51.333
<i>you know. you're getting
too old for that.</i>

613
00:29:51.466 --> 00:29:52.934
<i>You're just going
to damage your body.</i>

614
00:29:53.068 --> 00:29:56.071
<i>and I guess it's true.
but you get stubborn.</i>

615
00:29:56.204 --> 00:29:57.839
<i>And it just reminds me</i>

616
00:29:57.972 --> 00:30:00.742
<i>of someone
like Mors Kochanski.</i>

617
00:30:00.875 --> 00:30:02.377
<i>and last time I saw him.</i>

618
00:30:02.510 --> 00:30:05.480
<i>before he died there.
he was in a wheelchair</i>

619
00:30:05.613 --> 00:30:07.682
<i>but you could still
talk to him.</i>

620
00:30:07.816 --> 00:30:10.618
<i>and he'd tell you
stories for hours.</i>

621
00:30:10.752 --> 00:30:12.887
<i>and it was like he just wished
he could have got out</i>

622
00:30:13.021 --> 00:30:14.189
<i>of that wheelchair</i>

623
00:30:14.322 --> 00:30:16.257
<i>and headed off in the bush.
you know?</i>

624
00:30:16.391 --> 00:30:18.359
<i>And I guess
I'm that kind of guy.</i>

625
00:30:18.526 --> 00:30:20.395
<i>I just don't know
when to quit.</i>

626
00:30:20.528 --> 00:30:23.498
Oh. there's no room
to work in here.

627
00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:28.069
Oh. boy.
and every tree you touch.

628
00:30:28.203 --> 00:30:30.138
you're just getting showered.

629
00:30:31.573 --> 00:30:33.274
Let go off my hair. now.

630
00:30:36.511 --> 00:30:37.512
Oh. man.

631
00:30:37.645 --> 00:30:40.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

632
00:30:41.116 --> 00:30:42.951
I'm getting really frustrated.

633
00:30:43.084 --> 00:30:44.719
<i>♪ ♪</i>

634
00:30:44.853 --> 00:30:48.623
Wet. tired. hungry. cold.

635
00:30:48.757 --> 00:30:50.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

636
00:30:50.358 --> 00:30:54.262
<i>I find this very déjà vu-ish.</i>

637
00:30:54.395 --> 00:30:57.766
<i>It just brings Patagonia
right back to mind.</i>

638
00:30:57.899 --> 00:30:59.267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

639
00:30:59.401 --> 00:31:01.369
<i>It brings a lot of
anxiety with it too</i>

640
00:31:01.503 --> 00:31:05.039
<i>because think that. "Oh. man.
I got to do 50 days again."</i>

641
00:31:05.173 --> 00:31:07.709
<i>And I remember
how much I suffered.</i>

642
00:31:07.842 --> 00:31:11.346
<i>Took me three months
to recover from that.</i>

643
00:31:11.479 --> 00:31:14.349
<i>and that's what's got me
a bit nervous too.</i>

644
00:31:14.482 --> 00:31:16.050
<i>As you know.
in Patagonia.</i>

645
00:31:16.184 --> 00:31:18.453
hypothermia
was my enemy there.

646
00:31:18.586 --> 00:31:20.622
I don't need
that again either.

647
00:31:20.755 --> 00:31:23.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

648
00:31:23.525 --> 00:31:25.193
Wet. wet stuff.

649
00:31:25.360 --> 00:31:26.995
<i>♪ ♪</i>

650
00:31:30.965 --> 00:31:33.935
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

651
00:31:34.068 --> 00:31:41.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

652
00:31:49.217 --> 00:31:52.587
<i>- The sleeping bag
isn't too bad for wetness.</i>

653
00:31:53.922 --> 00:31:56.457
But it sure took forever
to dry that sleeping bag out.

654
00:31:56.591 --> 00:31:58.426
Boy. that was a worry.

655
00:31:58.560 --> 00:32:00.795
A real worry. I can tell you.

656
00:32:02.997 --> 00:32:04.566
So let's get breakfast.

657
00:32:07.101 --> 00:32:10.939
There's not much
to these little mussels.

658
00:32:11.072 --> 00:32:13.675
I'm going to have
to try today

659
00:32:13.808 --> 00:32:15.477
to set up a trap
for these seagulls

660
00:32:15.610 --> 00:32:18.279
that come through in low tide.

661
00:32:18.413 --> 00:32:21.549
So today. that is
one project I'm gonna do.

662
00:32:21.683 --> 00:32:23.284
is try to set up a trap

663
00:32:23.418 --> 00:32:24.786
and catch one of the seagulls

664
00:32:24.919 --> 00:32:26.120
so maybe I can have some meat.

665
00:32:27.755 --> 00:32:29.224
<i>Let's go build us a bird trap.</i>

666
00:32:29.357 --> 00:32:35.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

667
00:32:36.130 --> 00:32:38.399
<i>As far as food goes.</i>

668
00:32:38.533 --> 00:32:40.168
<i>can't catch fish.</i>

669
00:32:40.301 --> 00:32:43.238
<i>but you're going to see
that I've developed some ideas</i>

670
00:32:43.371 --> 00:32:45.306
<i>to make it easier on myself.</i>

671
00:32:45.440 --> 00:32:48.676
<i>so I don't have to struggle
for food as much.</i>

672
00:32:48.810 --> 00:32:52.580
When they bite.
the trigger comes back.

673
00:32:52.714 --> 00:32:56.451
<i>and put the bait further
from the trap itself.</i>

674
00:32:56.584 --> 00:32:59.387
<i>and then I want to run snares
at the bottom.</i>

675
00:32:59.521 --> 00:33:01.322
<i>loops at the bottom</i>

676
00:33:01.456 --> 00:33:02.790
<i>where the seagull's
gonna be stepping.</i>

677
00:33:02.924 --> 00:33:05.994
<i>and hopefully his feet
are in one of the loops.</i>

678
00:33:06.127 --> 00:33:07.629
<i>so when he picks the bait.</i>

679
00:33:07.762 --> 00:33:10.498
<i>the trap goes off
and tightens the snares</i>

680
00:33:10.632 --> 00:33:12.066
<i>around his legs.</i>

681
00:33:12.200 --> 00:33:13.735
<i>is the whole idea
of this trap.</i>

682
00:33:13.868 --> 00:33:15.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

683
00:33:15.370 --> 00:33:18.539
You see how we got our mussel.

684
00:33:18.673 --> 00:33:19.841
our trigger.

685
00:33:19.974 --> 00:33:22.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

686
00:33:22.243 --> 00:33:23.611
I always like
trying new ideas.

687
00:33:23.745 --> 00:33:26.247
but whether it works
or not we'll see.

688
00:33:26.381 --> 00:33:28.950
<i>You never know with your ideas
unless you try.</i>

689
00:33:30.118 --> 00:33:37.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

690
00:33:45.466 --> 00:33:49.003
- My plans for today...

691
00:33:49.137 --> 00:33:50.972
hopefully this
rain will hold off.

692
00:33:51.105 --> 00:33:52.840
<i>but regardless.</i>

693
00:33:52.974 --> 00:33:56.778
<i>I'm going to go
collecting food.</i>

694
00:33:56.911 --> 00:33:58.947
I'm hoping
there's just gonna be

695
00:33:59.080 --> 00:34:01.349
tons of mussels
and periwinkles

696
00:34:01.482 --> 00:34:02.917
and little crabs.

697
00:34:03.051 --> 00:34:06.788
and so I'm just gonna
fill this whole sucker

698
00:34:06.921 --> 00:34:09.557
<i>and kind of have
a big feast today.</i>

699
00:34:09.691 --> 00:34:11.292
<i>♪ ♪</i>

700
00:34:11.426 --> 00:34:14.195
<i>I got to say. it's a real
shock to the system</i>

701
00:34:14.329 --> 00:34:16.030
<i>to do this.</i>

702
00:34:16.164 --> 00:34:20.101
Dang. that's cold. wet.

703
00:34:20.234 --> 00:34:23.404
<i>So hopefully. I'm adjusting.</i>

704
00:34:23.538 --> 00:34:25.907
<i>but hopefully. I can also get
a lot more food</i>

705
00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:27.675
<i>so that I don't get
to that point</i>

706
00:34:27.809 --> 00:34:30.645
<i>of. like. dizziness
and fatigue</i>

707
00:34:30.778 --> 00:34:32.747
<i>like I did in Chilko.</i>

708
00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:35.049
That's where
I got a clam last time.

709
00:34:35.183 --> 00:34:37.919
so just hoping for more.

710
00:34:38.052 --> 00:34:40.621
I could see
these little divots.

711
00:34:40.755 --> 00:34:43.925
I could tell
where the clam holes were.

712
00:34:44.058 --> 00:34:46.928
<i>My mom was raised
on a farm in Maine.</i>

713
00:34:47.061 --> 00:34:48.596
<i>She was of the mindset</i>

714
00:34:48.730 --> 00:34:50.965
<i>that kids should play outside</i>

715
00:34:51.099 --> 00:34:53.468
<i>and get dirty
and have adventures.</i>

716
00:34:53.601 --> 00:34:56.371
<i>so I had
that free-range childhood.</i>

717
00:34:56.504 --> 00:34:57.839
Mussels.

718
00:34:57.972 --> 00:34:59.173
<i>♪ ♪</i>

719
00:35:06.347 --> 00:35:10.518
<i>I had a lot of unscheduled.
amazing time</i>

720
00:35:10.651 --> 00:35:13.154
<i>in nature.
as much as I wanted.</i>

721
00:35:13.287 --> 00:35:15.056
These are always
the motherload.

722
00:35:15.189 --> 00:35:16.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

723
00:35:16.891 --> 00:35:20.561
<i>I more kind of wanted to be
like Laura Ingalls Wilder.</i>

724
00:35:20.695 --> 00:35:23.731
<i>and my mom taught me
about the stars.</i>

725
00:35:23.865 --> 00:35:24.999
<i>about wild edibles.</i>

726
00:35:25.133 --> 00:35:26.734
<i>how to fish.</i>

727
00:35:26.868 --> 00:35:29.203
<i>We grew a lot of our food.
and we canned.</i>

728
00:35:29.337 --> 00:35:31.673
<i>and the connection
with food sources</i>

729
00:35:31.806 --> 00:35:33.841
<i>was always big in our family.</i>

730
00:35:33.975 --> 00:35:35.710
<i>so I feel really grateful</i>

731
00:35:35.843 --> 00:35:37.512
<i>for this level</i>

732
00:35:37.645 --> 00:35:39.480
<i>of clams and mussels.</i>

733
00:35:42.984 --> 00:35:47.121
So I have a ton of stuff.

734
00:35:47.255 --> 00:35:49.023
chock full of nuts.

735
00:35:49.157 --> 00:35:51.125
And I got some clams.
as you can see.

736
00:35:51.259 --> 00:35:52.927
They're so delicate.

737
00:35:53.061 --> 00:35:55.897
Look at the size of that thing.

738
00:35:56.030 --> 00:35:58.499
Dang. look at it.

739
00:35:58.633 --> 00:36:00.935
It's got barnacles
growing on it.

740
00:36:01.069 --> 00:36:03.371
It's a monster.

741
00:36:03.504 --> 00:36:06.274
I am definitely so grateful

742
00:36:06.407 --> 00:36:08.376
for the food today.

743
00:36:08.509 --> 00:36:10.645
If I can keep this going...

744
00:36:10.778 --> 00:36:12.880
<i>I'm going to make it
to 50 days</i>

745
00:36:13.014 --> 00:36:14.182
<i>in better condition</i>

746
00:36:14.315 --> 00:36:17.251
<i>than I was
at 21 days at Chilko.</i>

747
00:36:17.385 --> 00:36:24.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

748
00:36:35.002 --> 00:36:37.105
<i>- The no food is not fun.</i>

749
00:36:37.238 --> 00:36:39.006
<i>The wet bedding is no fun.</i>

750
00:36:39.140 --> 00:36:40.675
<i>Knowing what's in the future</i>

751
00:36:40.808 --> 00:36:42.543
<i>with the weather
getting worse.</i>

752
00:36:42.677 --> 00:36:46.013
<i>all I've got is mussels
and spruce bough tea.</i>

753
00:36:46.147 --> 00:36:47.682
<i>If there's any chance</i>

754
00:36:47.815 --> 00:36:50.518
<i>of getting
some substantial food.</i>

755
00:36:50.651 --> 00:36:52.954
<i>it would totally be
a game changer.</i>

756
00:36:53.087 --> 00:36:54.755
<i>I hear birds. seagulls.</i>

757
00:36:54.889 --> 00:36:58.159
<i>so I'm going to go check
that seagull trap.</i>

758
00:36:58.292 --> 00:37:00.361
<i>Hopefully.
we'll have something</i>

759
00:37:00.495 --> 00:37:02.063
<i>other than mussels tonight.</i>

760
00:37:06.134 --> 00:37:07.435
Oh. [bleep].

761
00:37:12.073 --> 00:37:15.643
It looks like I didn't put
my trap high enough up.

762
00:37:15.777 --> 00:37:18.546
So our trigger stick stayed.

763
00:37:18.679 --> 00:37:21.883
but over here.

764
00:37:22.016 --> 00:37:24.619
the one post

765
00:37:24.752 --> 00:37:27.722
washed out of the ground.

766
00:37:27.855 --> 00:37:31.325
and our trigger system's
sitting there.

767
00:37:31.459 --> 00:37:33.227
I thought
it was up high enough.

768
00:37:34.829 --> 00:37:36.998
I'm wasting my time now.
I think.

769
00:37:37.131 --> 00:37:40.401
if it's going to come up
and just wash everything out.

770
00:37:40.535 --> 00:37:42.136
A lot of work for nothing. eh?

771
00:37:42.270 --> 00:37:44.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

772
00:37:45.039 --> 00:37:48.209
<i>I anticipated there was
gonna be enough food here.</i>

773
00:37:48.342 --> 00:37:50.111
<i>but I'm finding out different.</i>

774
00:37:50.244 --> 00:37:53.114
<i>and it's very stressful</i>

775
00:37:53.247 --> 00:37:55.650
<i>as just not being able to eat.</i>

776
00:37:59.120 --> 00:38:00.855
<i>Not in bad health yet.</i>

777
00:38:00.988 --> 00:38:03.691
<i>but it's only going to get
worse down the road here</i>

778
00:38:03.825 --> 00:38:05.293
<i>with the resources that I see.</i>

779
00:38:05.426 --> 00:38:07.428
<i>so it's stressful</i>

780
00:38:07.562 --> 00:38:09.630
<i>thinking that things
can only get worse.</i>

781
00:38:09.764 --> 00:38:12.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

782
00:38:16.671 --> 00:38:19.540
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

783
00:38:19.674 --> 00:38:26.647
<i>♪ ♪</i>

784
00:38:40.962 --> 00:38:43.898
- So today started

785
00:38:44.031 --> 00:38:46.934
by feeling really sick.

786
00:38:47.068 --> 00:38:49.370
and that was kind of scary.

787
00:38:50.738 --> 00:38:53.507
Felt weak. felt nauseous.

788
00:38:53.641 --> 00:38:57.011
<i>So I just drank
quite a bit of water.</i>

789
00:38:57.144 --> 00:38:58.813
<i>I'm feeling a little better.</i>

790
00:38:58.946 --> 00:39:02.283
<i>which is good because I still
have a lot of work to do.</i>

791
00:39:02.416 --> 00:39:06.420
<i>So today. I need to really
get some firewood going</i>

792
00:39:06.554 --> 00:39:07.889
<i>and bring it into the shelter</i>

793
00:39:08.022 --> 00:39:10.891
<i>and just sort of store it
in all the. you know.</i>

794
00:39:11.025 --> 00:39:12.226
<i>nooks and crannies.</i>

795
00:39:12.360 --> 00:39:14.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

796
00:39:20.601 --> 00:39:24.205
<i>I'll just soldier on
for right now.</i>

797
00:39:24.338 --> 00:39:27.308
<i>and hopefully it will pass</i>

798
00:39:27.441 --> 00:39:29.010
<i>once I get working.</i>

799
00:39:29.143 --> 00:39:30.411
<i>It could be hunger.</i>

800
00:39:30.544 --> 00:39:34.181
<i>but I think it would be
more like stomach pain...</i>

801
00:39:34.315 --> 00:39:35.516
<i>♪ ♪</i>

802
00:39:35.650 --> 00:39:37.718
<i>Rather than nausea.</i>

803
00:39:37.852 --> 00:39:41.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

804
00:39:41.255 --> 00:39:43.824
<i>- Man. I'm getting soaked.</i>

805
00:39:43.958 --> 00:39:46.427
I am pretty concerned
about my tarp.

806
00:39:46.560 --> 00:39:48.095
Check it out.

807
00:39:48.229 --> 00:39:49.964
Wherever you can see light

808
00:39:50.097 --> 00:39:52.967
are spots that I've got holes

809
00:39:53.100 --> 00:39:54.201
in the tarp.

810
00:39:54.335 --> 00:39:57.605
Not ideal.
more where that came from.

811
00:39:57.738 --> 00:40:01.842
Water. water. water.

812
00:40:01.976 --> 00:40:04.679
That is not what
we want in a roof.

813
00:40:04.812 --> 00:40:06.180
<i>I've got to be honest.</i>

814
00:40:06.314 --> 00:40:08.316
<i>this is so much
more challenging</i>

815
00:40:08.449 --> 00:40:09.684
<i>than I figured it would be.</i>

816
00:40:09.817 --> 00:40:14.255
<i>♪ ♪</i>

817
00:40:14.388 --> 00:40:18.059
- I wish I could have gotten
that bird trap set up.

818
00:40:18.192 --> 00:40:20.428
<i>The stress of not having</i>

819
00:40:20.561 --> 00:40:23.064
<i>the food that I need is just--</i>

820
00:40:23.197 --> 00:40:25.032
<i>I'm getting these
panic attacks.</i>

821
00:40:25.166 --> 00:40:27.802
<i>these anxieties
that just pop out of nowhere</i>

822
00:40:27.935 --> 00:40:29.670
<i>for no reason. stress.</i>

823
00:40:29.804 --> 00:40:31.372
<i>♪ ♪</i>

824
00:40:31.505 --> 00:40:34.842
<i>So this is much harder
than I thought it would be.</i>

825
00:40:38.279 --> 00:40:39.880
<i>- Cold and wet and miserable.</i>

826
00:40:40.014 --> 00:40:41.615
<i>and nearly hypothermic.</i>

827
00:40:41.749 --> 00:40:44.385
that's just not how
I want it to be.

828
00:40:44.518 --> 00:40:46.487
<i>♪ ♪</i>

829
00:40:46.620 --> 00:40:49.357
I'm thinking about
all of the things in my life

830
00:40:49.490 --> 00:40:52.093
that I put on hold
and just disappeared from

831
00:40:52.226 --> 00:40:53.828
to have this experience.

832
00:40:53.961 --> 00:40:56.764
It's a really different
situation for me now.

833
00:40:56.897 --> 00:41:00.067
I'm thinking about
my beautiful life at home.

834
00:41:00.201 --> 00:41:01.769
I'm thinking
about my sweetheart a lot

835
00:41:01.902 --> 00:41:03.070
<i>and my family.</i>

836
00:41:03.204 --> 00:41:05.272
<i>Never
in a million years thought</i>

837
00:41:05.406 --> 00:41:07.108
<i>that I would be
considering leaving</i>

838
00:41:07.241 --> 00:41:09.543
<i>as early as day six.</i>

839
00:41:09.677 --> 00:41:12.880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

840
00:41:13.013 --> 00:41:15.883
<i>- It's only day six.
but I'm really struggling.</i>

841
00:41:16.017 --> 00:41:17.718
This just brings me back.

842
00:41:17.852 --> 00:41:22.223
kind of déjà vu-type situation
to Patagonia.

843
00:41:22.356 --> 00:41:24.925
<i>and I remember
how much I struggled</i>

844
00:41:25.059 --> 00:41:27.027
<i>and suffered over there.</i>

845
00:41:27.161 --> 00:41:29.063
and I think
that's creating my anxiety.

846
00:41:29.196 --> 00:41:31.932
realizing that I have to do
the same thing here.

847
00:41:32.066 --> 00:41:35.336
<i>I'm just not ready
for suffering like this again.</i>

848
00:41:35.469 --> 00:41:38.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

849
00:41:38.773 --> 00:41:40.775
<i>- Sick to my stomach
right now.</i>

850
00:41:40.908 --> 00:41:42.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

851
00:41:43.043 --> 00:41:46.180
<i>Just going to pause
for a second. whew.</i>

852
00:41:46.313 --> 00:41:48.149
<i>My mind is. of course. racing.</i>

853
00:41:48.282 --> 00:41:51.585
<i>thinking about
what this could be.</i>

854
00:41:51.719 --> 00:41:53.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

855
00:41:53.254 --> 00:41:54.522
<i>I got to go get water.</i>

856
00:41:54.655 --> 00:41:57.825
<i>♪ ♪</i>

857
00:41:57.958 --> 00:41:59.560
<i>I don't know what's going on.</i>

858
00:41:59.693 --> 00:42:03.564
<i>♪ ♪</i>

859
00:42:03.697 --> 00:42:06.734
<i>- This is much harder
than I thought it would be.</i>

860
00:42:06.867 --> 00:42:09.303
<i>and I keep getting
anxiety attacks.</i>

861
00:42:09.437 --> 00:42:11.772
<i>- Oh. [bleep].
[coughing]</i>

862
00:42:11.906 --> 00:42:14.208
I just pepper sprayed
my bed.

863
00:42:14.341 --> 00:42:18.212
- Yep. you just stay
right there cussing at me.

864
00:42:18.345 --> 00:42:20.214
<i>- Sometimes you know
you're getting close</i>

865
00:42:20.347 --> 00:42:21.449
<i>to your edge...</i>

866
00:42:23.184 --> 00:42:25.853
<i>But we can be
so mentally strong</i>

867
00:42:25.986 --> 00:42:28.055
<i>that we just want
to keep going.</i>

868
00:42:28.189 --> 00:42:29.590
<i>Oh.</i>

869
00:42:32.660 --> 00:42:34.195
[ice cracking]
